The Camenae, of whom Egeria was one, were Roman divinities, whose name is connected with carmen (an oracle or prophecy), whence we also find the forms casmenae, Gamenae, and Carmentis. The Camenae were accordingly prophetie nymphe, and they belonged to the religion of ancient Italy, although later traditione represent them as having been introduced into Italy from Arcadia.
